Cerebral palsy (CP) is a group of permanent movement disorders that appear in early childhood. Signs and symptoms vary among people and over time. Stay tuned for future episodes dropping every Friday and Monday leading up to the 20th anniversary of continuous human presence on the International Space Station on Nov. 2, 2020. #SpaceStation20th
